Overview

[Psa 62:1](../../../bib/kjv/psa062.htm#001.md), David, professing his
confidence in God, discourages his enemies; [Psa
62:5](../../../bib/kjv/psa062.htm#005.md), In the same confidence he
encourages the godly; [Psa 62:9](../../../bib/kjv/psa062.htm#009.md), No
trust is to be put in worldly things; [Psa
62:11](../../../bib/kjv/psa062.htm#011.md), Power and mercy belong to God.

